<div1 type="letter">

<fw>Robert Silliman Hillyer</fw>

<note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
<note type="curatorial">9</note>

<opener>
<address>
<addrLine>Newark R. D. B, Delaware</addrLine>
</address>
<dateline>1 August 1960</dateline>
<salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
</opener>

<p>If you have not decided on a candidate for The Academy Fellowship, may I suggest Howard Nemerov? At forty, he seems to me the best poet of his generation, infusing old forms with marvelous power and sweetness. And at this point in his career he needs encouragement for further achievement.</p>

<p>In any case, I am glad to have this opportunity to send you my greetings.</p>

<closer><salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
<signed>Robert Hillyer</signed>

</closer>

</div1>
</body>

